description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen which would support an enthusiastic Occupational Therapist to consolidate and develop robust assessment and intervention skills in an inpatient setting. Based in the fast-paced Adults of Working Age Mental Health Inpatient setting in Royal Glamorgan Hospital - covering assessment and treatment wards, and input into the Psychiatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The OT service has a well embedded model of care and offers the opportunity to practice core skills based work within a robust multi-disciplinary setting. There is scope to deliver both individual and group based interventions (though service delivery must adhere to all Covid related guidelines at the present time). This post also involves some community work opportunities to facilitate comprehensive assessments and to inform discharge processes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post benefits from well established supervision and support systems, plus participation in audit and service development processes. You will have the opportunity to be proactively involved in the supervision of other staff members, and will enjoy excellent working relationships with Occupational Therapy colleagues working in the community setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The clinical team on this site includes a Band 7 OT, this post, a rotational Band 5 post and a Band 3 OT Support Worker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lynette Hibbert - Band 7 Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contactable at Lynette.Hibbert@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Angela Arentsen - Principal Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
